          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Louis</placeName>
                                        <date>Jan 26<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5604</date>.</p>
                              <p>Dear Sir!</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">The Directors of our Bnai-El Congregation,
                                        elected<lb/> at our last annual meeting, whose names you
                                        will see by the<lb/> enclosed list, have directed me to send
                                        you our subscriptions<lb/> List and to express to you their
                                        hope, that you will exert<lb/> yourself in behalf of our
                                        purpose; thus far we have succeeded<lb/> in getting a pretty
                                        good subscription here and if a little more<lb/> can be
                                        collected we will soon be able to go to building</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Though there is frequently but little gained if
                                        there stands<lb/> a <sic>beautifull</sic> house dedicated to
                                        the service of God it is of<lb/> great moment for our people
                                        here.</p>
                              <p>As you will have perceived during your last visit to this city
                                        and<lb/> by your editorial experience, the interest which is
                                        felt or<lb/> manifested here for our religion, our
                                        literature c is far below<lb/> that of any other place in
                                        proportion to its great <sic>jewish</sic><lb/> population,
                                        but it is no utopian hope, that if a respectable<lb/>
                                        Synagogue is soon built, many who do not belong now to<lb/>
                                        any <sic>israel</sic>. Congregation will join us, and so
                                        will probably the<lb/> others, now inactive congregation,
                                        either as a whole or as indivi<lb/>duals; more interest will
                                        then be felt in our affairs and from<lb/> this a better
                                        future may be anticipated.</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>The lot we bought from <persName>Mr Jacobs</persName> for the
                                        Synagogue was sold<lb/> by the same far below its real
                                        value, in consideration of its<lb/> purpose, it has a front
                                        of 70 feet (by 75 in depth) its location is<lb/> central and
                                        it is our plan to erect a plain but handsome building,<lb/>
                                        the cost of which shall not exceed $6000 including fixtures,
                                        and<lb/> it shall at the same time have school Rooms for
                                        religious instruction.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Any contribution, small as the amount may be, will
                                        therefore be<lb/> thankfully received and be of great
                                        benefit towards a speedy<lb/> accomplishment of these
                                        designs.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I do not think of anything else that might be of
                                        interest<lb/> for you, except that some of our Israelites,
                                        though foremost<lb/> in contributing for the relief of the
                                        suffering emigrants<lb/> desained[?] as and about
                                                  <placeName>Cairo</placeName> by [?]ce, have made
                                        among themselves<lb/> besides this an extra collection and
                                        handed $100.00 as<lb/> a present of a Jewish society for the
                                        same purpose to the<lb/> mayor of this city.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">With feelings of confidence in your zeal that
                                        will<lb/> leave this call go lost, and with the assurance
                                        of<lb/> my perfect esteem and affection</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">Yours</p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">
                                        <persName role="author">Isidor Bush</persName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
